  "text": "The challenge of contextually ranking nodes in a network has emerged as a problem of canonical significance in many domains, with a particularly rich history of study in social and information networks [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . An active line of recent work has focused on the problem of seed set expansion in networks [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] [CITATION_8] [CITATION_9] [CITATION_10] [CITATION_11] , a fundamental version of node ranking with the following natural definition.",
